<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[192,1441,291,1691]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,397,1379,1403]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name means “handsome or imposing” and refers to this species’ large size and bright color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[240,1181,1443,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="30.[192,1441,291,1691]" box="[240,1181,1443,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,630,1443,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Distribution and phenology.</emphasis>
The species is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1067,1177,1443,1467]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[192,1441,291,1691]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,595,1475,1499]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis and discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[601,901,1475,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis box="[601,901,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Porphyrogenes speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the larger species of the genus. The valva, especially the long and upcurved harpe, of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[792,937,1508,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis box="[792,937,1508,1531]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to this structure of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1297,1401,1508,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stresa">
<emphasis box="[1297,1401,1508,1531]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. stresa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moschler" baseAuthorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zohra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. zohra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[324,435,1540,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sparus">
<emphasis box="[324,435,1540,1563]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. sparus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the costa-ampulla is broader and more quadrate than on any of those species. In addition, the uncus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[462,607,1572,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis box="[462,607,1572,1595]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is longer than on those species. The valva of 
<taxonomicName box="[1151,1235,1571,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sula">
<emphasis box="[1151,1235,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. sula</emphasis>
